HEADWORD: Potamian
<hw>Po*ta"mi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
river.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A river tortoise; one of a group
of tortoises (<fam>Potamites</fam>, or <fam>Trionychoidea</fam>) having
a soft shell, webbed feet, and a sharp beak. See
<er>Trionyx</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

